post_text:
April 1 is National Census Day!

Why should you fill out the Census? Do it for your children!

The 2020 Census count impacts the federal funds that communities receive each year for programs and services that are critical for schools, students, and younger children, such as:

•Special education, Head Start, after-school programs, and classroom technology.
•Food assistance, including free and reduced-price school lunches.
•Maternal and child health programs

How can you be counted in the Census while maintaining social distancing?

It can be filled out on-line by clicking the following link: https://2020census.gov

Based on the most recent information on COVID-19, Komarek School District 94 will be closed from 3:30 p.m. on March 13 through Monday, April 6, 2020. The current plan is for students and staff to return on Tuesday, April 7, 2020.

Although this situation is unlike anything we have navigated in the past, the health and safety of our students and community will always remain at the forefront of our decisions. I appreciate your understanding.

Sincerely,

Brian J. Ganan

post_text:
The week of March 9th-March 13th Komarek is celebrating Respect week. NJHS is partnering with Special Olympics Illinois to put on these great events. Each day we will celebrate in a different way.

On Monday, we will be holding Sports Day. Team Up
Against Bullying by wearing your favorite sports wear!

Tuesday is Twin Day. Show that you’ve Got a Friend in Me
by matching with your friends.

Wednesday is Pajama Day! Put Bullying to Rest and show
up to school in your PJ’s!

Thursday, dress in your Favorite Color. Let’s end bullying
with One Day and One Color!

Friday is Komarek Spirit Day. Show your school spirit and
help Komarek Stand Up Against Bullying!

A message from Dr. Gold regarding parent-teacher conferences:

Our spring parent-teacher conferences are this Friday, February 14th, 2020. A letter went home to K-5 parents either requesting or not requesting a conference with the teacher. If a conference was requested, please on the link below to sign up for a time slot with the appropriate teacher. These conferences are important, and we value the time to meet with our families. The sign up closes on Wednesday, February 12th, 2020, so please make sure to sign up if requested. Mrs. Sopata (x100) in the school office can assist with sign up if you are unable to reach the link.

Thank you,

Jason Gold

If a conference was requested, please on the link below to sign up for a time slot with the appropriate teacher. These conferences are important, and we value the time to meet with our families. The sign up closes on Wednesday, February 12th, 2020, so please make sure to sign up if requested. Mrs. Sopata (x100) in the school office can assist with sign up if you are unable to reach the link.

Thank you,

Jason Gold

https://www.signupgenius.com/tabs/43075d60fa3ceedc35-parent

post_text: Our next Komarek fundraising event will be at Lou Malnati’s in Broadview Square on Tuesday, October 22nd from 4-10pm. If you have not yet registered your child for the upcoming 2019-2020 school year, you will need to make an appointment with Mrs. Anderson in the District Office starting on August 1, 2019. Please call Mrs. Anderson at 708-447-8030 x101.

To save time during your appointment, parents/guardians of returning students can complete the registration forms online prior to their appointment. An e-mail was sent to parents/guardians of all returning students on July 11, 2019. If you did not receive the e-mail, please contact Mr. Trakas in the Technology Office at 708-447-8030 x119 or via e-mail at atrakas@komarek94.org.

You will need to provide proof of residence at your appointment.

Please do not hesitate to contact Mrs. Anderson at 708-447-8030 x101 or via e-mail at ganderson@komarek94.org with any questions or concerns you might have.

PowerSchool has now been set up for the upcoming 2019-2020 school year. With this completed, the PowerSchool parent and student portal is now back online for parents of students in grades 5 through 8.

You can access the portal either through the web at komarek94.powerschool.com or you can download the PowerSchool app for Apple iOS or Android. Your credentials will remain the same as those you used last school year.

If you have any difficulty accessing your PowerSchool account, please do not hesitate to reach out to me by either replying to this e-mail message or calling Komarek’s Technology Office at 708-447-8030 x119.

Have a great day!

post_text: On May 15-16 our 8th Grade Class of 2019 visited our state capital, Springfield. They visited the current Capitol, the Old State Capitol, Lincoln's Tomb, the Abraham Lincoln Presidential Library and Museum, Lincoln's Home and the IL Military Museum. Also, as a special treat, they were able to take a photo and meet with a State Senator on the Senate Floor. It was a fun, educational, memorable experience for our graduates!!!

post_text: We extend our deepest sympathy to the family of former Komarek District 94 Principal and Superintendent, Neil Pellicci. Mr. Pellicci passed away suddenly on Wednesday, June 5th. Neil touched the lives of so many. He will be truly missed by all who have passed through the halls of Komarek.

post_text: If you have not yet registered your child for our 2019 Summer Enrichment Program, the deadline is May 17, 2019. The Program offers children an opportunity for fun, creativity, and learning. Some of our class offerings include: Volleyball, Addition & Subtraction Boot Camp, Dungeons & Dragons Camp, and Kids Yoga. The program begins on June 17. Please visit the Komarek School website at www.komarekschool.org for more information.
